{"title":"MADE Show: Sinewave Cycles Compact Dynamo Rear Light, No Dynamo Hub or Front Light Needed","link":"https://bikerumor.com/sinewave-cycles-compact-dynamo-rear-light/","date":1724882729000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Taillight-on-stand-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" alt=\"(Photos / Ron Frazelle)\" /></p>\n<p>This last weekend in Portland at the MADE Show, we got to see a bunch of really amazing people. And they were showing off their amazing talents. Including dynamo light guru/aficionado, David Dean of <a href=\"https://www.sinewavecycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sinewave Cycles</a>. This year at the show, he was showing off the new Sinewave Cycles Taillight. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles compact and handesome\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-compact-and-handesome-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Sinewave Cycles Taillight can connect to a front dynamo light, or battery, or even be used on an eBike. But, it has another very unique feature. Most, if not all of the rear dynamo lights available on the market need a front dynamo light to work. But, the new Sinewave Cycles Taillight does not. It can be run directly to the front dynamo hub.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles left one is blinking 1\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-1-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Blinking…. off….</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles left one is blinking\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-left-one-is-blinking-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>…. on. </figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Perfect for those that don’t need/want/like front dynamo lights. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When run straight to the dynamo hub, it allows the Snewave Cycles Taillight to be “always on”. No need to mess with chargers or batteries, you just have a working rear light that’s ready to shine as soon as the front wheel is turning. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles mounting option\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-mounting-option-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Clever and simple mounting hole. </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles simple mounting sollution\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-simple-mounting-sollution-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Simple Mounting solution</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Taillight has an optional blinking mode and a stand light that remains illuminated for 5 minutes after the bike has stopped. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Taillight Innovative Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Powered by headlight, battery, or directly from the dynamo hub</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Selectable blinking mode</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrated reflector</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flexible installation options</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Waterproof</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Made in the USA</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s.jpeg\" alt=\"MADE Coverage Sinewave Cycles Beacon 2s\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MADE-Coverage-Sinewave-Cycles-Beacon-2s-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I am a massive fan of the Sinewave Cycles Beacon 2, and you can read about it in <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-sinewave-beacon-2-dynamo-bicycle-light/\" target=\"_blank\">my review</a>. I would imagine that it is a sound bet that the new Taillight will be of equal build quality, with the same technological innovation. If you like what you see and want to learn about Dynamo products, check out their site by hitting the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.sinewavecycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SinewaveCycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sinewave-cycles-compact-dynamo-rear-light/\">MADE Show: Sinewave Cycles Compact Dynamo Rear Light, No Dynamo Hub or Front Light Needed</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteH